               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-1580" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1580" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1580" type="surname" value="FREEMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1580" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS FREEMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a licensed victualler. On the 12th of March, the prisoner came to my place for half a pint of porter—I served him—he gave me a bad shilling—I gave him into custody—I marked the shilling—there were two other persons there—I kept it on the bar till I had served him, but it was in my sight all the time.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-1581" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1581" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1581" type="surname" value="DRODGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1581" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM DRODGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. On the 12th of March I took the prisoner, and received this shilling from Freeman—the prisoner was dis<lb></lb>charged, there being no other case against him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-1582" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1582" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1582" type="surname" value="HOLDER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1582" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN HOLDER</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep the Crown and Thistle, in South-Lambeth. On the 16th of March the prisoner came for some ale—he gave me a half-crown—I gave him 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 4 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>. change—I put the half-crown into the till—there was no other there—my wife soon called my attention to it, and I found it was bad—on the 30th of May the prisoner came again, and gave my wife a half-crown—I received it from her—I sent for an officer, and gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-1583" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1583" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1583" type="surname" value="HOLDER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1583" type="given" value="RHODA"></interp>RHODA HOLDER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of John Holder. On the 16th of March the prisoner called for a glass of ale—I after that called my husband's atten<lb></lb>tion to the half-crown I found in the till—on the 30th the prisoner called again for half a pint of porter, and gave me a bad half-crown—I gave it my husband.</p>
               <p>
